data.title: Dancing With The Stars' Peta Murgatroyd welcomes third child
data.meta_description: Dancing With The Stars' Peta Murgatroyd has welcomed her third child into the world with husband Maksim Chmerkovskiy.
data.text:
Dancing With The Stars' Peta Murgatroyd and her husband Maksim Chmerkovskiy have welcomed their third child into the world.

Maksim, who is 44, announced the birth on social media on Friday, writing: "He is officially evicted from his mom and he is sooooo cute!!!!"

The proud father noted that the birth took "around 47 seconds total" and "exactly one push."

The couple, who are both professional dancers, began their relationship in the early 2010s.

They have two other sons: Shai, 7, and Rio, who is 13 months old.

The duo married in New York in 2018.

Peta, who is 37, has been open about experiencing multiple miscarriages and undergoing IVF treatments before conceiving their second child naturally in 2023.

Taking to Instagram fans voiced their feeling on the birth.

One fan wrote: "A huge Congratulations another handsome little man."

A second fan noted: "Glad to hear baby and mama are doing well. Congratulations on your little boy!"

A third joked: "Gosh…I wished I looked that good after delivering …I looked like the Michelin man"

Peta announced her third pregnancy in February 2024 via social media.

In a video, she revealed the news to her husband through FaceTime, discussing the need for a larger home and showing him positive pregnancy tests.

The dancer told People magazine in 2023 that her second pregnancy had been "a whirlwind" and "the best blessing for us, truly."
